			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	The SoundCloud Community is continuing to grow and we&rsquo;re looking to expand our team that supports it. Here at SoundCloud, our Community comes first &mdash; they&rsquo;re the fuel in our engine! So we do our very best to aid our community in the most efficient way possible.</p>
<p>
	People like a quick response that resolves their issue, but above all, really enjoy when someone takes the time to address everything they&rsquo;ve asked and are concerned about. Our goal is to leave our members feeling satisfied and elated after they receive our response. For us, every interaction with a SoundCloud member counts.</p>
<p>
	As part of the Community Support team, you will play a key role in advancing our support culture. We&rsquo;re looking for someone who is analytical and empathetic, willing to be a SoundCloud member&rsquo;s internal advocate and finds genuine motivation in helping people.</p>
<p>
	<br />
	The ideal candidate:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		You know SoundCloud like the back of your hand (in-line with the company&rsquo;s mission and extremely familiar with the site)</li>
	<li>
		You love and are great at solving problems</li>
	<li>
		You have outstanding written and verbal communication skills</li>
	<li>
		You care, you&rsquo;re considerate and detail-oriented</li>
	<li>
		You&rsquo;re a team player and also great at working independently</li>
	<li>
		You have a strong affinity for technology</li>
	<li>
		You&rsquo;re curious and proactive</li>
	<li>
		You have, or can obtain, authorization to work in Germany</li>
	<li>
		Work well under stress</li>
	<li>
		You have completed a University Bachelor degree</li>
</ul>
<p>
	Responsibilities:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Support our Community in all support tiers (including social media), prioritize accordingly</li>
	<li>
		Occasionally work weekend support shifts</li>
	<li>
		Be strategic: identify bottlenecks early, suggest and implement solutions</li>
	<li>
		Help troubleshoot issues and file bugs</li>
</ul>
<p>
	To apply:<br />
	Record an audio message to:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		introduce yourself</li>
	<li>
		reflect on the points above to tell us why you think you&rsquo;re the perfect candidate</li>
	<li>
		tell us how you can contribute to and improve the support experience</li>
</ul>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	Use the timed comments to link us to your profiles on the web (SoundCloud, Blog, Twitter, etc) and include the private link to the recording in your cover letter.</p>
<p>
	Cover letters that include a link to your audio message will be prioritized in the application process.<br />
	&nbsp;</p>
